    <h1>Male Endomorph Diet</h1>

    <!-- Body Description Section -->
    <h2>Body Description</h2>
    <p>Physical Characteristics: Men with an endomorph body type tend to have a wider, stockier build with a thicker neck, waist, and hips. They typically have a higher body fat percentage, making it easier to gain weight but harder to lose it. They often have a high strength potential due to natural muscle mass.</p>

    <!-- Food List Section -->
    <h2>Food List</h2>
    <h3>Carbohydrates:</h3>
    <p>Low glycemic options like quinoa, oats, whole-grain bread, and sweet potatoes in moderation.</p>
    <h3>Proteins:</h3>
    <p>Lean sources such as chicken breast, turkey, fish, egg whites, and plant-based proteins like lentils.</p>
    <h3>Healthy Fats:</h3>
    <p>Avocado, nuts in moderation, olive oil, and seeds.</p>
    <h3>Fruits & Vegetables:</h3>
    <p>Fiber-rich options like leafy greens, broccoli, carrots, apples, and berries.</p>

